<subSubSection id="C346651CFF92EB5954C5FA40B68B3E72" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE33697FF92EB5954C5FA40B68B3E72" blockId="43.[151,1436,1410,1698]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB5954C5FA40B5363E02" bold="true" box="[198,328,1522,1548]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D14FF92EB595556FA41B6003E02" authority="Bosmans &amp; Cardoso &amp; Crespo, 2010" authorityName="Bosmans &amp; Cardoso &amp; Crespo" authorityYear="2010" box="[341,638,1523,1548]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pelecopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monsantensis" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB595556FA41B6003E02" box="[341,638,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Pelecopsis monsantensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57FEFF92EB595688FA40B7633E02" box="[651,797,1522,1548]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinghuished from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D14FF92EB595090FA41B10C3E02" box="[1171,1394,1522,1548]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pelecopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB595090FA41B16E3E02" box="[1171,1296,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Pelecopsis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by combined characters of the shape of the prosoma and the structure of the male palp. The prosoma has a cephalic tubercle with a large sulcus behind the eyes, generally much smaller in other species and the palpal tibia has a twisted base, straight in all other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C346651CFF92EB5F54C5F935B5D03A29" lastPageId="45" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE33697FF92EB5954C5F935B0E43EAC" blockId="43.[151,1436,1410,1698]" box="[198,1178,1671,1698]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB5954C5F935B51E3EAF" bold="true" box="[198,352,1671,1697]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Description:</emphasis>
Male: Measurements: Total length 2.0; prosoma 0.75 long, 0.71 wide.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF23661FFF92EB595494F8A8B59B3FBF" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" startId="43.[151,271,1818,1842]">
<paragraph id="8BE33697FF92EB595494F8A8B59B3FBF" blockId="43.[151,1436,1818,1969]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB595494F8A8B5103F3C" bold="true" box="[151,366,1818,1842]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">FIGURES 94–104.</emphasis>
Figs 94–98. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D14FF92EB5955FCF8A8B7973F3F" authority="Bosmans &amp; Crespo" authorityName="Bosmans &amp; Cardoso &amp; Crespo" authorityYear="2010" box="[511,1001,1818,1841]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pelecopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monsantensis" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB5955FCF8A8B7733F3F" box="[511,781,1818,1841]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Pelecopsis monsantensis</emphasis>
Bosmans &amp; Crespo
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57FEFF92EB5957F3F8A8B0093F3F" box="[1008,1143,1818,1841]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 94. Male prosoma, lateral view; 95. Idem, dorsal view; 96. Male palp, prolateral view; 97. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 98. Embolic division, anteroventral view. Figs 99–104. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D14FF92EB595602F8E8B7F83F7F" authority="(Simon, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[513,902,1882,1905]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pelecopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susannae">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF92EB595602F8E8B69E3F7F" box="[513,736,1882,1905]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Pelecopsis susannae</emphasis>
(Simon, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
; 99. Male prosoma, lateral view; 100. Male palp, prolateral view; 101. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 102. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 103. Epigynum, ventral view; 104. Vulva, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE33697FF94EB5F54C5FF25B6AB3A0C" blockId="45.[151,1436,151,663]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF94EB5F54C5FF25B55938BF" bold="true" box="[198,295,151,177]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Colour:</emphasis>
Prosoma orange brown, paler at margins; legs yellowish orange; abdomen dark grey, with dark purplish brown, strongly denticulate scutum covering 9/10 of the abdomen. Prosoma (
<figureCitation id="13672A12FF94EB5F5090FF0FB16138D9" box="[1171,1311,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–104" captionStartId="43.[151,271,1818,1842]" captionText="FIGURES 94–104. Figs 94–98. Pelecopsis monsantensis Bosmans &amp; Crespo new species; 94. Male prosoma, lateral view; 95. Idem, dorsal view; 96. Male palp, prolateral view; 97. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 98. Embolic division, anteroventral view. Figs 99–104. Pelecopsis susannae (Simon, 1914); 99. Male prosoma, lateral view; 100. Male palp, prolateral view; 101. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 102. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 103. Epigynum, ventral view; 104. Vulva, ventral view." pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs 94–95</figureCitation>
): Cephalic part with large, rounded lobe carrying the PM, with strong concavity between AM and PM and with large sulcus behind the PL; cephalic lobe with long erect hairs, eye region with short, oblique hairs; thoracic part coriaceous towards the margin, with punctuated striae. Eyes: a = 1, b = 1.5, c = 2, d = 3. Chelicerae: Fang groove with 3 promarginal and 3 small retromarginal teeth; stridulating file hardly perceptible, with 21–23 files. Sternum: Smooth. Legs: Tibiae spineless; Tb Mt I = 0.64; Tb Mt IV absent. Palp (
<figureCitation id="13672A12FF94EB5F50B8FECAB137399C" box="[1211,1353,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–104" captionStartId="43.[151,271,1818,1842]" captionText="FIGURES 94–104. Figs 94–98. Pelecopsis monsantensis Bosmans &amp; Crespo new species; 94. Male prosoma, lateral view; 95. Idem, dorsal view; 96. Male palp, prolateral view; 97. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 98. Embolic division, anteroventral view. Figs 99–104. Pelecopsis susannae (Simon, 1914); 99. Male prosoma, lateral view; 100. Male palp, prolateral view; 101. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 102. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 103. Epigynum, ventral view; 104. Vulva, ventral view." pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs 96–98</figureCitation>
): Tibia twisted at its base, with elongate dorsal apophysis with terminal hook and short, hooked retrolateral apophysis; cymbium with small basal hump; tegulum with large, triangular protegulum; embolus spirally coiled, describing 2.5 circles, terminally pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE33697FF94EB5F54C5FDBFB5D03A29" blockId="45.[151,1436,151,663]" box="[198,430,525,551]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B928EA85FF94EB5F54C5FDBFB5553A29" bold="true" box="[198,299,525,551]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Female:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
